  "content": "A subgraph is an independent GraphQL service with its own schema and resolvers. Subgraphs can retrieve data from the Reactor (via `subgraph.reactorClient`), relational data stores, or analytics stores. They consist of a schema (GraphQL types/queries/mutations), resolvers (data fetching logic), and context fields (auth, external sources). Generated via `ph generate --subgraph <name>`, they auto-register at `/graphql/<name>`. The supergraph gateway at `/graphql` combines all subgraphs (except the drive subgraph at `/d/:driveId`) into a single endpoint, enabling federated queries across document models and custom subgraphs in one request.",
